result.execSummary:
The defendant Jarod J Winkels was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-THC (<=200 grams) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)1.
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ma] Case called at 10:53am 
Defendant Jarod J Winkels in court.  Attorney Karl E Huebner in court for Jarod J Winkels.  Attorney Monica Hall in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of " NO CONTEST " entered on Counts #6 and #9; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified.  The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads in and dismisses: Counts #7 and #8

Sentencing arguments/recommendations given by Counsel

On Count #6, the Court withholds sentence and places the Defendant on Probation for 3 years, with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling per Agent
--random drug and/or alcohol screening
--to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program per Agent
--no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--take any and all prescription medications only as prescribed by treating prescriber
--if permitted to travel out of State, no possession or use of marijuana(THC) in states where it is legal. No legal CBD products or other legal cannabis derivatives without express written permission of agent
--no contact with Jarred Coy
--to comply with DNA sample provision 
--payment of costs, fees and surcharges, to include $125 drug testing fees(joint & several) and attorney fees as to both Counts #6 and #9


On Count #9: The Court sentences Defendant to serve 30  days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges; to commence on 8/6/22 by NOON.
--1 day credit for time already served given
--Mr. Winkels is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
The Court orders the Defendant to comply with DNA sample provision.

The Court finds society would not be harmed, and Mr. Winkels would benefit from special disposition upon successful completion of entire probation term. 
recess: 11:10am
